<DOC><DOCNO> DOE1-23-1055 </DOCNO><TEXT>In a method for the selective separation of carbon dioxide from a streamof acid gas containing carbon dioxide and sulfur containing acid gascomponents including hydrogen sulfide the improvement is described whichcomprises the steps of: countercurrently contacting the gas stream inan absorption zone with a treating agent to thereby selectively removea substantial portion of the carbon dioxide from the gas stream by absorptioninto the treating agent, discharging a gas stream from the absorptionzone containing a significantly reduced amount of carbon dioxide anddischarging the treating agent enriched with absorbed carbon dioxidefrom the absorption zone, the treating agent being an aqueous solutioncontaining from about 35 wt. % to about 55 wt. % of a polyoxypropylenetriamine. The polyoxypropylene triamine has a molecular weight of about320 to about 475 and the aqueous solution having an amine concentrationof about 2.5 to about 3.5 meq/g.</TEXT></DOC>